  "body": "# üêû Bug Report\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nCurrently if we initialize a libp2p host without initializing the peer manager in time, this could \r\ncause a panic.\r\n\r\nBug Found By Antithesis.\r\n\r\n### Has this worked before in a previous version?\r\n\r\nN.A\r\n\r\n## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction\r\n\r\nIt would be possible to trigger this for nodes running via a preknown/static identity at startup. If they are constantly dialed in from\r\ninbound peers.\r\n\r\n## üî• Error\r\n\r\n```\r\npanic: runtime error: invalid memory address or nil pointer dereference\r\nsegmentation violation code=0x1 addr=0x50 pc=0x14ed43e]\r\n\r\ngoroutine 222 [running]:\r\ngithub.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/v3/beacon-chain/p2p.(*Service).isPeerAtLimit(0xc000312900, 0x1)\r\n/git/src/github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/beacon-chain/p2p/discovery.go:460 +0x3e\r\ngithub.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/v3/beacon-chain/p2p.(*Service).InterceptAccept(0xc000312900, {0x7f6d3a0b6d60, 0xc0037abb00})\r\n/git/src/github.com/prysmaticlabs/prysm/beacon-chain/p2p/connection_gater.go:56 +0xa5\r\n[github.com/libp2p/go-libp2p/p2p/net/upgrader.(*listener).handleIncoming(0xc0002101c0)\r\n/root/go/pkg/mod/github.com/libp2p/go-libp2p@v0.20.3/p2p/net/upgrader/listener.go:87 +0x172\r\ncreated by github.com/libp2p/go-libp2p/p2p/net/upgrader.(*upgrader).UpgradeListener\r\n/root/go/pkg/mod/github.com/libp2p/go-libp2p@v0.20.3/p2p/net/upgrader/upgrader.go:111 +0x225\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n**What version of Prysm are you running? (Which release)**\r\n\r\n`57b7e0b57252eacd79ea64b5a25c6ab32ee42da9`\r\n\r\n",
